    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="423"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName type="from">Baron Fava</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                            >Hill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-12-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Having been instructed by my Government to reorganize the Italian immigration
                    bureau before December 30, it is necessary that I should be informed without
                    delay whether the scheme mentioned in my letter 14th<note n="1" xml:id="d423fn1"
                        >See note of December 21, 1899.</note> instant to Mr. Adee finds no
                    objection.</p>
                <p>I ask in favor of the agent of the Italian consulate but the same admission to
                    Barge Office under under the same conditions granted to the agent of the
                    Austrian consulate.</p>
                <p>Please wire me. Thanks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baron Fava.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
